## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="c69e9-102">Режим ввода для <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument> определяется его <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.Mode%2A> свойством.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c69e9-102">The input mode for an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument> is determined by its <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.Mode%2A> property.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c69e9-103">Режим ввода по умолчанию — Voice, который указывает, что грамматика, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument> определенная параметром, будет соответствовать речевому входу.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c69e9-103">The default input mode is Voice, which indicates that the grammar defined by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument> will match speech input.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c69e9-104">Режим DTMF указывает, что грамматика будет соответствовать тонам с двумя тонами (DTMF) вместо речи.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c69e9-104">The Dtmf mode indicates that a grammar will match Dual-Tone Multi-Frequency (DTMF) tones instead of speech.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c69e9-105">Существует 16 тонов DTMF, 12 из которых обычно находятся на большинстве телефонов.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c69e9-105">There are 16 DTMF tones, 12 of which are commonly found on most telephones.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c69e9-106">При <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> создании объекта <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument>на основе объект будет <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.Mode%2A> соответствовать типу входных данных, заданных свойством, который получает экземпляр <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsGrammarMode>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c69e9-106">When you create a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> object from an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument>, the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> object will match the type of input specified by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsDocument.Mode%2A> property, which gets an instance of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsGrammarMode>.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
  
```csharp  
string srgsDocumentFile = Path.Combine(Path.GetTempPath(), "srgsDocumentFile.xml");  
SrgsDocument document = null;  
GrammarBuilder builder = null;  
Grammar grammar = null;  
  
Choices firstThree = new Choices(new string[] {"1", "2", "3"});  
Choices nextThree = new Choices(new string[] {"4", "5", "6"});  
Choices lastThree = new Choices(new string[] {"7", "8", "9"});  
  
Choices keyPadChoices = new Choices(new GrammarBuilder[] {firstThree, nextThree, lastThree, new Choices("0")});  
  
builder = new GrammarBuilder(keyPadChoices);  
document = new SrgsDocument(builder);  
  
document.Mode = SrgsGrammarMode.Dtmf;  
grammar = new Grammar(document);   
```
